folder: West End Avenue & 104th Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
895 West End Avenue at S.W. corner of 104th Street, "The Mentone," an apartment house built between 1910 and 1916 and replacing five small houses which were the original buildings on the site, built in the mid 1890's.

The house on the S.E. corner will be demolished early in 1924 and replaced by a modern apartment house.
About 1922.

Gift of E. M. Jenks.

folder: West End Avenue & 104th Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
905 West End Avenue, on N.W. corner of 104th Street, a new apartment
building erected about 1918.
The house on the N.E. corner, partly shown in the picture, is 900 West End Avenue, built in the mid 1890's. Between 1925 and 1930
it will be replaced by an apartment building.
This photograph was taken simultaneously with that of the S.W.
corner opposite.
About 1922.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
NEG # 3772
